cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new variant of Projected Gradient Descent (PGD) for crafting adversarial attacks on neural networks. This is a common topic in the fields of machine learning and computer vision, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG and cs.CV sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the computational efficiency of the proposed method, which could also place it in the cs.CR sub-category. The use of stochastic methods and the focus on crafting attacks could also suggest the cs.AI and cs.NE sub-categories as likely options.
